        "entity_or_term": "الرحمن",
        "notes": "The mention of 'al-Raḥmān' (The Merciful) refers to a supreme deity, a name used in pre-Islamic Arabia, particularly in South Arabia, for a monotheistic or supreme God."
      },
      {
        "poem_id": "suwayd_b_abī_kāhil_026",
