        "entity_or_term": "اللَهُ",
        "notes": "The reference to 'Allāh' (God) as the one who raises and lowers indicates a belief in a supreme divine agent, consistent with pre-Islamic Arabian monotheistic or henotheistic concepts."
      },
      {
        "poem_id": "suwayd_b_abī_kāhil_026",
        "verse_indices": [
