        "category": "Deities_and_Oaths",
        "entity_or_term": "اللَهِ",
        "notes": "The phrases 'niʿamun li-Llāhi' (blessings from God) and 'ṣanīʿu Llāhi' (God's doing) refer to God as the source of blessings and actions, aligning with pre-Islamic supreme deity concepts."
      },
      {
